PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F309A1782400703
OL,3,CReeves backs Burnham for PM despite
OL,4,Cspeculation of who will be next
OL,5,Cchancellor
OL,7,FOn Wednesday, Downing Street confirmed
OL,8,Fthat Starmer intends to continue as an
OL,9,FMP on the back benches for the rest of
OL,10,Fthis Parliament but would not take a
OL,11,FCabinet job if offered.
OL,13,FOther senior Labour figures, including
OL,14,Fformer transport secretary Louise
OL,15,FHaigh, foreign secretary Yvette
OL,16,FCooper, and former health secretary
OL,17,FWes Streeting, have all been tipped
OL,18,Ffor top jobs in a government led by
OL,19,FBurnham.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
